\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 24. C. clementei} Boiss. ex DC., {\i Prodr.}{\b  7}: 303 (1838). Stems 30-50 cm, simple or sparingly branched at apex, lanate. Leaves white-tomentose, pinnatisect; lower with broadly ovate, irregularly lobed and denticulate segments, petiolate; upper sessile, often simple, lobed. Involucre c. 25 mm in diameter, globose; bracts broadly ovate, glabrous to sparsely lanate; appendages ovate-triangular, the fimbriae 3-5 mm. Florets yellow, the outer as long as the inner. Achenes c. 5 mm; pappus c. 5 mm.{\i  Calcareous rocks. • Mountains of S.W. Spain.} Hs.
