\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 29. C. prolongi} Boiss. ex DC., {\i Prodr.}{\b  7}: 303 (1838). Stems 20-50 cm, simple or sparingly branched. Leaves subglabrous; basal lanceolate, entire; lower cauline lyrate-pinnatifid, acute, long-petiolate, with few linear-lanceolate, mucronulate, entire segments. Involucre 15-18 mm in diameter, ovoid; appendages broadly triangular, semilunate at base, not completely covering the broadly ovate bracts, with a brown apical spine up to 4 mm; fimbriae c. 2 mm. Florets deep golden or orange. Achenes c. 3 mm, sericeous, rarely glabrous; pappus 2-5 mm, white.{\i  Rocky ground and heaths. • S.W. Spain, S.Portugal.} Hs Lu.
